parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of exhaust manifold studs can cause exhaust gas leaks, noise problems, and carbon monoxide issues, which can lead to safety risks and health problems.
Warped exhaust manifolds can cause exhaust manifold studs to break, leading to exhaust gas leaks, noise problems, and carbon monoxide issues, which can lead to safety risks and health problems.
Premature and repeated transmission failure can cause unexpected loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Timing belt failure can cause engine failure, leading to unexpected loss of power, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.

the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission fails to shift into reverse.
